main event: Two distinct bright and shiny objects were tracked by radar at Wheelus Air Base, Libya on October 13, 1956.
interesting points: The objects were at an estimated altitude of 30,000 feet with visibility up to 250 miles., The objects appeared to be traveling at approximately 3000 mph and made several direction changes., Radar of the 633rd Radar Squadron and 431st Fighter Interceptor Squadron tracked the objects., Visual contact was not established by pilots despite radar evidence., The report states there was insufficient data for a conclusive evaluation.
witness description: No visual contact made by pilots despite radar indications.
